</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6761368BB3E618A8E7F47C0DD820B609" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3C313409D9D6ED99A06598DC970C336E" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC6A0E9E6A69578AE47926FB621222A6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Together with 
<taxonomicName id="31DA1BCE506E98B9F336A8286933FCD6" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota luederitzensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luederitzensis">
<emphasis id="82A0A17D8A1C90F7E994BA5CFA458FAC" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pampsilota luederitzensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also from southwest Africa, 
<taxonomicName id="442AA0CEC77168C2A5A70920C95CC90C" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota brandbergensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandbergensis">
<emphasis id="1C0C6F0CB2C2A0E06C4BF0F28C79A236" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pampsilota brandbergensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other 
<taxonomicName id="2D3C9A21BD86C4EC40BDC261FAA10F7C" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9B23F4F9FC2040FDA5A77CEBE01B20E7" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pampsilota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its body length of maximally 6.0 mm (other species at least 7.0 mm long). The yellow pronotum and entirely black legs of 
<taxonomicName id="C730BC3F121D3D2E01E72E0387825D61" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota brandbergensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandbergensis">
<emphasis id="987D9362F1AAB312F2AB991C130A1AA9" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pampsilota brandbergensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distinguish it immediately from 
<taxonomicName id="ABC4D737D079F400AA994F583BC29FCD" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota luederitzensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luederitzensis">
<emphasis id="DA120E8F82B806D894A80B91F29DEBDD" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pampsilota luederitzensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with dark pronotum and largely pale tibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B9077B35E90E17B937DE9C4FE7CB3780" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="8E666A62FCD7558AE56AB2D3F4D3F951" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D99E1AC17E9AF94CD50B1EF1824A8BAB" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Variability in colour pattern is scarcely noticeable in the two known specimens, except that tergum 5 as well as sterna 3-5 may be entirely yellow, and the pronotum may have a small ventro-lateral blackish spot.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
